{"data":{"project":{"html":"<p>I created a smart mirror for my apartment. This display hangs in my apartment and displays information useful at a glance--current time and date, the day's weather forecast, personal calendar events, nearby subway times, Citibike dock availability, and daily scheduled reminders.</p>\n<h4>V1 (2016)</h4>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/8576a/mirror-v1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Mirror V1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/893a4/mirror-v1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/bbf57/mirror-v1.jpg 200w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/260b8/mirror-v1.jpg 400w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/893a4/mirror-v1.jpg 800w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/25965/mirror-v1.jpg 1200w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/e54c8/mirror-v1.jpg 1600w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/7c0ed/mirror-v1.jpg 2400w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/8576a/mirror-v1.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>I created the first non-interactive prototype using an old Dell netbook, plastic two-way mirror, and a custom-made wooden frame.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/8576a/mirror-v1-inside.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Mirror V1 Inside\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/893a4/mirror-v1-inside.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/bbf57/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 200w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/260b8/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 400w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/893a4/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 800w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/25965/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 1200w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/e54c8/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 1600w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/7c0ed/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 2400w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/8576a/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>The software ran a Node.js server on the backend and a React.js front-end. Glancing at it while getting ready quickly became a part of my morning routine.</p>\n<h4>V2 (2018)</h4>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/8576a/mirror-v2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Mirror V2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/893a4/mirror-v2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/bbf57/mirror-v2.jpg 200w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/260b8/mirror-v2.jpg 400w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/893a4/mirror-v2.jpg 800w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/25965/mirror-v2.jpg 1200w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/e54c8/mirror-v2.jpg 1600w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/7c0ed/mirror-v2.jpg 2400w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/8576a/mirror-v2.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>The newest version is interactive via voice recognition (albeit a very crude version of it, currently). It is an Electron app running on Raspberry Pi that also utilizes React.js for the UI and has a much larger 1080p display.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Mirror","link":null,"tags":null,"github":"https://github.com/aamaliaa/mirror","image":null,"created":"February 2018"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/mirror/"}}